Wife and daughter of a traditional ruler in Oyo State, Oba Olusanjo Ojo, the Baba-Aso of Igboole in Igboora area, who were kidnapped on Monday have regained their freedom. DAILY POST gathered that they regained their freedom on Wednesday. Some unknown gunmen suspected to be kidnappers had on Monday abducted Olori Funbi Ojo, wife of Oba Olusanjo Ojo and her daughter. Mrs. Ojo, our correspondent gathered is the current Matron of Oyo State College of Agriculture and Technology (OYSCATECH) Igboora Health Centre. Ojo and her daughter, a trained nurse and a serving National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) member, were kidnapped around 8.15 pm on Monday while returning from the college where she worked, but her son who drove the bullet-ridden vehicle was lucky as he escaped being captured by the suspected kidnappers. The kidnapped victims have so far regained their freedom. They were said to have been released on Wednesday. Public Relations Officer (PPRO) of the State Police Command, Mr. Olugbenga Fadeyi told DAILY POST that the kidnapped victims have been released. Fadeyi in a short message made available to DAILY POST on Thursday noted that concerted efforts of the police and other stakeholders led to the release of the abductees. “Concerted efforts of the police teams with collaboration with critical stakeholders (Community leaders, vigilantes, hunters etc) paid off and the victims were released and reunited with their family members”.